      "content": "The established neighborhood likely offers more predictable returns, as the existing wealthy residents tend to stay put and maintain property values. The rapidly changing, high-density area, however, presents a higher risk because the influx of different groups can lead to unpredictable neighborhood dynamics and potential instability. While the turnover might suggest quick rental income, the long-term stability is questionable when the community itself is in flux.",
